results.name: Triangle T(n,k) read by rows, where T(n,k) = number of times the determinant of a real n X n (0,1)-matrix takes the value k, for n >= 1, 0 <= k <= A003432(n).
comment: The first 4 rows were provided by _Wouter Meeussen_.
example: a(4)=T(2,1)=3 because there are 3 different (0,1)-matrices with det=1:
xref: Cf. T(n, 0)=A046747(n), T(n, 1)=A086264(n), T(n, A003432(n))=A051752(n). The n-th row of the table contains A089472(n) nonzero entries.
